means: 预知，预见( foresee的现在分词 )

sentence.Network_en: The commission is cautiously favourable to Austrian membership, foreseeing few economic problems.
sentence.Network_cn: 没有预见到什么经济问题，委员会谨慎地赞同吸收奥地利为会员。

sentence.Network_en: Policymakers in Europe have had equal problems in foreseeing events.
sentence.Network_cn: 欧洲政策制定者在预测上也是半斤八两.

sentence.Network_en: I seem to deem his foreseeing of that the man will seek seeds in the weed.
sentence.Network_cn: 我似乎相信他的预见,他预见那个人将在杂草中寻找种子.

entry.def: If you foresee something, you expect and believe that it will happen.

example.ex: He did not foresee any problems...
example.tran: 他没有预见到任何问题。

example.ex: ...a dangerous situation which could have been foreseen...
example.tran: 原本可以预见到的危险情况
